<TITLE> Three killed, 32 injured in road crashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 4 (bdnews24.com)--Three people were killed and 32 others injured on Friday in two road accidents in Rangpur and Barisal . Two persons died and around 30 others injured early morning when a Nilphamari-bound bus coming from Dhaka turned upside down in Post Office area of Mithapukur Upazila in Rangpur. One of the two killed was identified as Nipati Chandra Deb, 26, of Kamarpara of Jaldhaka Upazila in Nilphamari. The other's identity could not be known immediately. The injured were admitted to Rangpur Medical College Hospital. Din Mohammad, a sub-inspector of Baradarga Highway Police Station, said the accident occurred as the bus lost control because of slippery highway due to rainfall at night. A retired BDR soldier was crushed under the wheels of a truck in Rupatali Gas Turbine area of Barisal City at around 9am. Two others were injured in the accident. Traffic police inspector Jalil Ahmed said former Aziz Khan, 60, of South Rupatali, and two others were taking preparation to go to Patuakhali by motorbike from Gas Turbine area in the morning when a speedy truck ran them over. Aziz died on the spot. The injured were admitted to Shebachim Hospital with serious injuries. Police seized the truck but its driver and his assistant managed to flee. Local people blocked the highway for sometime in protest at the murder. bdnews
